  "texts": [
    "Various aspects of the phenomenology of states within the QH ferromagnetic manifold disagree with experiment, suggesting that we need to look further.",
    "Rather than moving directly to tackle the full many-body problem, for which techniques are limited, it is reasonable to first investigate a wider range of Slater determinants, i.e.",
    "enlarge our considerations to a broader class of mean-field states.",
    "In other words, the central premise we adopt is that as we add perturbations such as strain to move away from the strong coupling picture, the ground state leaves the manifold of strong-coupling ferromagnets, but the Hartree-Fock approximation that it is faithfully described by a Slater determinant holds true.What sorts of states should we consider?",
    "An initial guess is to consider orders that break moiré translational invariance."
  ],
